## Three lines of defence

The three lines of defence (3LoD) model aims to clarify the relationship between risk takers and the internal control functions, and provides all employees within the bank with clarity regarding their risk management responsibilities. The three lines of defence model is applied across all risk types and covers the whole organisation, including the client units, functions, the Risk Management organisation, outsourced activities and distribution channels.

